Description: Fragment of a heavily corroded iron artefact, possibly part of a key (?) with two parallel wards and beginning of a curved shank .
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Tell Dafana, North-west Ptolemaic mound ?
Curator's comments: Corrosion makes the item hardly identifiable; the interpretation as part of a key comes from the Museum register (wards of a key ?"). The Ptolemaic dating indicated in the register would suggest a provenance from the North-west Ptolemaic mound.
Bibliographic references: Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.77, p.185, pl.27)
